--- Kathy and Paul <pa.ka(-at-)verizon.net> wrote:
> Andrew,
>    It's a commom problem with VW buses for the
> starter not to work after a drive that is long
> enough for the engine heat to get the starter hot. 
> Some people live with it and do the 'bang on the
> starter' routine, some install an extra relay to
> work around the starter solenoid, but I've found
> that a once a year sevicing of the starter and
> electrical system prevents the problem.
> 
